President Obama will honor the latest recipients of the National Medal of Science and National Medal of Technology and Innovation, which are the highest honors for achievement and leadership in the fields of science and technology. The awardees will receive their medals at a White House ceremony early next year. The National Medal of Science recognizes individuals who have made outstanding contributions to science and engineering, while the National Medal of Technology and Innovation recognizes those who have made lasting contributions to America's competitiveness and quality of life. The recipients include prominent scientists and innovators from various universities and institutions across the country.